{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"span":3,"markdown":"ANC1 volumes rose through 2024 before dipping in early 2025 and returning to around ~70,000 visits by mid-year.

ANC4 showed stable but lower volumes, with a slight increase over time, between ~20,000 and ~25,000 monthly visits since 2023. 

Addressing gaps between first and fourth visits remains critical to ensure continuity of care and improved antenatal outcomes."},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"aa5cd9f0-2de7-449e-93c0-943adbd9ee72","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in antenatal care"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"Across regions, consistency remains strong overall. 

Nationally, ANC1 vs. ANC4 consistency is very high (100%), with all regions meeting the benchmark. However, Penta1 vs. Penta3 consistency is weaker, averaging 94% and dropping as low as 75% in Mudug (Galmudug) and Hiiraan regions, underscoring where data plausibility checks are most critical.

"},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"94f96848-5e34-425b-a09e-79ec325393ed","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Internal consistency"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"At the national level, the mean DQA score remained stable, decreasing slightly from 95% in 2022 to 93% in 2025. National mean scores are high, showing that on average, Somalia's HMIS data is close to the desired quality standard.

Across districts, all scores remained above 80% in 2025.

Although many facility-months don’t meet all criteria, they are close on average — suggesting that small improvements in reporting practices could bring most facilities above the threshold."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"da716f6b-abd4-4a55-b149-56a4454b29da","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in data quality"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":0.8,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"Data completeness is variable across regions and indicators, with antenatal care, delivery by skilled birth attendant, BCG, Penta1 and Penta 3 vaccination, and outpatient visits reporting above 90% completeness across most regions. 

Several indicators, including PNC visit for mothers and newborns, and delivery by caesarian section often fall below 90%.

Weaker reporting in Benadir, Middle Shebelle, Gedo, Lower Juba, Ayn, Sool and Lower Shabelle regions suggests the need for targeted improvements in regional reporting."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.6,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"b64d2c67-35c5-413b-a035-c425cf9ce243","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Reporting completeness"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"At the national level, outliers remain low, with all indicators averaging below 2%, suggesting consistency in reporting quality across most services.

Outliers are slightly higher for a few indicators, particularly for Penta1 & Penta3 vaccination and outpatient visits.

Reporting is stable across most regions, though Hiraan, Middle Shebelle, Ayn, Karkaar, and Ras-Asayr have indicators with 3% or more observations flagged as outliers, suggesting localized reporting challenges rather than systemwide issues."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.6,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"e4c3a72a-fc9b-49ee-975e-f9de03cde153","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Outliers"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"span":3,"markdown":"Outpatient service utilization remained relatively stable from 2023 through mid-2025, averaging around 600,000 to 650,000 visits per month.

